---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: ""
description: "Senior Frontend Developer specializing in accessible interfaces, design systems, and front-end architecture."
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h1 class="hero__title" data-reveal>Fabrizio Palladino</h1>
    <p class="hero__subtitle" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">Senior Frontend Developer — HTML, CSS, JS/TS, Accessibility</p>
    <p class="hero__intro" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
      I build accessible, performant interfaces that put people first.
      With over a decade of experience, I focus on design systems, front-end architecture, and making the web work for everyone.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h2 data-reveal>What I Do</h2>
    <div class="grid" style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-md);">
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        <h3 class="card__title">Accessible Interfaces</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Hand-coded HTML and CSS to W3C standards with a strong understanding of WCAG. Ensuring the web is usable by everyone.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
        <h3 class="card__title">Design Systems</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Structured, scalable component libraries and style guides that keep teams aligned and code consistent.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
        <h3 class="card__title">Front-end Architecture</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Clean, maintainable codebases built with modern HTML, CSS, JavaScript and TypeScript. Performance matters.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="4">
        <h3 class="card__title">Wireframes &amp; Prototypes</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Translating ideas into interactive prototypes. Bridging the gap between design and development.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <div data-reveal>
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-sm);">
        After studying Management of Publishing Enterprises, I fell in love with HTML, CSS, and their potential.
        That passion broadened to include everything that makes the web usable, accessible, and reliable.
        I now build interfaces for institutions like the Council of the European Union, always focusing on the user first.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-sm);">
        <a href="/about/" class="cta-link">Learn more about me</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h2 data-reveal>Latest Posts</h2>
    <div style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-md);">
      {% set posts = collections.blog | reverse %}
      {% if posts.length > 0 %}
        {% for post in posts %}
          {% if loop.index <= 3 %}
            <div class="post-list__item" data-reveal>
              <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="post-list__link">
                <h3 class="post-list__title">{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
                <p class="post-list__meta">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</p>
                {% if post.data.description %}
                  <p class="post-list__description">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
                {% endif %}
              </a>
            </div>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
        <p data-reveal>Blog posts coming soon.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
